<p><b>Where can I find my Hyundai color code?</b> In most cases you will find the paint code in the door jamb: only a couple models feature it in either the radiator support or firewall. Paint codes are usually two digits long, and can contain both letters and numbers.</p>
<p><b>What is the color code for Hyundai Dark GREY?</b> Hyundai Dark Grey Code 2E Basecoat Spray Paint.</p>
<p><b>What is the color of the Hyundai logo?</b> Colors. Moving on to the color palette, Hyundai makes use of a simple tone of silver and blue. On a vehicle's grill, the logo in silver represents elegance, creativity, and perfection. In print or digital, the logo turns blue that stands for reliability, trust, excellence, and supremacy.</p>
<p><b>Where is the paint code on a Hyundai i10?</b> Hyundai paint codes are found in the vehicle. Specifically, Hyundai paint codes (or finding the Hyundai paint code from VIN) are usually found in the driver's-side door jamb.</p>
<p><b>Can I find color code by VIN number?</b> You can call your dealer, give them your VIN, and ask for the paint code. Another option is searching for paint codes online using your VIN. Though your VIN won't give you your car's exact paint code or color, it's a tool that will help you find it.</p>
<p><b>How do I find my colour code?</b> The paint code is sometimes printed near the VIN number, although you may need to look for it separately. Common paint code locations include the driver's side door jamb, in the boot and under the bonnet.</p>
<p><b>What is the Hyundai grey color called?</b> </p>
<p><b>What are car color codes?</b> Each car has a paint code that designates the correct shade of paint for its exterior. Sometimes, you can even find paint codes for different components, like the underside of the hood or accent colors. The paint code listed on your car, however, refers to the exterior body color.</p>
<p><b>What is my color code vehicle?</b> Driver's door label When you open the driver's door, a rectangular label is affixed either to the door edge or the B pillar. Along with the VIN and important information like GVWR, it often has the vehicle paint code printed on it.</p>
